# React Component Conventions

## Component shape
- Default-export a single PascalCase function component per file.
- Destructure props inline in the function signature.

```jsx
// ✅
export default function ChatMessage({ role, content, isError }) { ... }

// ❌
export default function ChatMessage(props) {
  const { role, content } = props
  ...
}
```

## State updates
Always use the functional updater form when new state depends on previous state:
```js
// ✅
setMessages((prev) => [...prev, newMessage])

// ❌
setMessages([...messages, newMessage])
```

## Callbacks
Wrap event handlers and callbacks in `useCallback`. Include all referenced state/props in the dependency array.

## Inline styles
Define style constants at the top of the file (not inline in JSX) when reused more than once:
```jsx
// ✅
const containerStyle = { display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 8 }
return <div style={containerStyle}>

// ❌ (only if reused)
return <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 8 }}>
```

## Chart and table components
`ChartRenderer` and `ResultTable` are rendering-only. Do not add data fetching, SSE subscriptions, or API calls to them.
